<div class="heads yellow">
    <h3>Rules of the Game</h3>
</div>

<div class="callout">

    <ul>
        <li>According to the rules of the poker game, each player makes bets before the cards are dealt. This condition is met in classic poker on the 1xBet website. There is also a second way, when only two players who are sitting near the dealer bet.
        </li>
        <li>All bets in poker are divided into mandatory and voluntary. Mandatory rates from the bank. And voluntary ones directly depend on the player's choice. He can raise the bet, or he can leave the game, refusing to raise. The bets that the participants make are called blind.
        </li>
        <li>Collecting cards in classic poker will turn out from those that are on hand. At the start of the game, everyone receives five cards and the acceptance of bets begins. After the end of the bidding, everyone has the right to change from one to five cards, or not to change anything.
        </li>
        <li>Then the final stage of the game session begins. Again, the players are betting, some refuse to raise. At the end, everyone opens the cards. The whole pot is taken by the participant who has the highest combination in his hands.
        </li>
    </ul>

</div>

<div class="heads brown">
    <h3>Combinations</h3>
</div>

<div class="callout">

    <p>For new players, it is important to know the basic combinations in poker and it is with them that you need to start learning the rules. It is not so difficult to learn and remember the features and names in reality, but you also need to learn how to see them during the game, evaluate the prospects, strength and collect the best combination of your cards. As mentioned above, the task of the participants is to collect the most winning combination. Here are the best combinations in five-card poker.
    </p>
    <p><b>In one game session, the player who has the highest combination wins.</b></p>
    <blockquote><b>IMPORTANT</b>
        <p>The strongest combination that can be formed is made up of the available cards. If the combination consists of two, three or four cards, it is supplemented with the highest-valued cards from the unused ones.</p>
    </blockquote>

</div>

